description: (Enterprise Tier Only) Commands to manage predefined accelerator in Azure Spring Apps.

commands.name: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator disable
commands.summary: (Enterprise Tier Only) Disable a predefined accelerator.
examples: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator disable --name AcceleratorName --service MyCluster --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator enable
commands.summary: (Enterprise Tier Only) Enable a predefined accelerator.
examples: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator enable --name AcceleratorName --service MyCluster --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator list
commands.summary: (Enterprise Tier Only) List all existing predefined accelerators.
examples: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator list --service MyCluster --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator show
commands.summary: (Enterprise Tier Only) Show the settings, provisioning status and runtime status of predefined accelerator.
examples: az spring application-accelerator predefined-accelerator show --name AcceleratorName --service MyCluster --resource-group MyResourceGroup
